body: @pravingadakh Thanks for reporing this issue. Let me check if I can reproduce it.
@harupy Were you able to reproduce it?
@pravingadakh I wasn't able to reproduce the issue with the latest version of MLflow. You can try MLflow 1.30.0.

@harupy The MLflow version (1.24.0) that we use is part of the managed offering at our organization and I can not change the version. Do you think I am missing anything here or if it is a legit issue then can we patch it or something?
Also do you think this is related to https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/issues/6450 issue?
I don't think you're missing anything.

@pravingadakh

Unfortunately, we don't have a plan to make a patch release for MLflow 1.24.
@harupy I wasn't expecting MLflow community to fix it. We just need help in identifying the root cause and maybe fix it ourselves.

@pravingadakh I ran this command, but I wasn't able to reproduce the error:

```bash
> cat a.py
from pyspark.ml import Pipeline
from pyspark.ml.classification import LogisticRegression
from pyspark.ml.feature import HashingTF, Tokenizer
import mlflow
from pyspark.sql import SparkSession

spark = SparkSession.builder.getOrCreate()
training = spark.createDataFrame(
    [
        (0, "a b c d e spark", 1.0),
        (1, "b d", 0.0),
        (2, "spark f g h", 1.0),
        (3, "hadoop mapreduce", 0.0),
    ],
    ["id", "text", "label"],
)
tokenizer = Tokenizer(inputCol="text", outputCol="words")
hashingTF = HashingTF(inputCol=tokenizer.getOutputCol(), outputCol="features")
lr = LogisticRegression(maxIter=10, regParam=0.001)
pipeline = Pipeline(stages=[tokenizer, hashingTF, lr])
model = pipeline.fit(training)

with mlflow.start_run():
    mi = mlflow.spark.log_model(model, "spark-model")
    mlflow.spark.load_model(mi.model_uri)


> docker run --rm -w /mlflow -v $(pwd)/a.py:/mlflow/a.py python:3.8 bash -c "apt update -y && apt install -y openjdk-11-jdk && pip install 'protobuf<4' mlflow==1.24.0 pyspark && python a.py"


```
Maybe your pyspark version is too old. MLflow only supports pyspark >= 3.0.
